Install Kali Linux and Yersinia through Virtual Machines (VMware) Step 1: Download Pre-built Virtual Machines of Kali 	Link: https://www.kali.org/get-kali/#kali-virtual-machines Step 2: Unzip and Open in VMware (change settings as needed for your device) 	Network Adapter should be NAT so it can connect to the internet. Step 3: Run the Kali Virtual Machine 	User: kali 	Pass: kali 	 	Default Credentials: https://www.kali.org/docs/introduction/default-credentials/ 	 Step 4: Install Yersinia by Opening a terminal 	commands: 		sudo su 		apt-get update 		 		apt remove --auto-remove yersinia	//optional - only if yersinia was prev installed 		apt purge --auto-remove yersinia	//optional - only if yersinia was prev installed 		 		git clone https://github.com/tomac/yersinia /opt/yersinia 		apt install autoconf libgtk-3-dev libnet1-dev libgtk2.0-dev libpcap-dev -y 		 		cd /opt/yersinia 		./autogen.sh 		 		./configure --with-gtk 		 		make 		make install 		 		yersinia - G 	 	 Extra: set LANCard to Bridge during labs